subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology. This species is named after Dr. Felix Kopstein (
1893­1939
), who contributed so much to our knowledge of the snake fauna of Indonesia . Several of the specimens we used for our studies were collected by him. He was also the first to report delayed fertilisation.
